values.label: Bill of exchange
values.comment: Document/message, issued and signed in conformity with the applicable legislation, which contains an unconditional order whereby the drawer directs the drawee to pay a definite sum of money to the payee or to his order, on demand or at a definite time, against the surrender of the document itself.

values.label: Promissory note
values.comment: Document/message, issued and signed in conformity with the applicable legislation, which contains an unconditional promise whereby the maker undertakes to pay a definite sum of money to the payee or to his order, on demand or at a definite time, against the surrender of the document itself.

values.label: Statement of account message
values.comment: Usage of STATAC-message.

values.label: Direct delivery (transport)
values.comment: Document/message ordering the direct delivery of goods/consignment from one means of transport into another means of transport in one movement.

values.label: WCO second step of two-step export declaration
values.comment: Second part of a simplified declaration, in accordance with the WCO Customs Data Model, to Customs by which goods are declared for Customs export procedure based on the 1999 Kyoto Convention.

values.label: WCO one-step import declaration
values.comment: Single step declaration, in accordance with the WCO Customs Data Model, to Customs by which goods are declared for Customs import procedure based on the 1999 Kyoto Convention.

values.label: WCO first step of two-step import declaration
values.comment: First part of a simplified declaration, in accordance with the WCO Customs Data Model, to Customs by which goods are declared for Customs import procedure based on the 1999 Kyoto Convention.

values.label: WCO second step of two-step import declaration
values.comment: Second part of a simplified declaration, in accordance with the WCO Customs Data Model, to Customs by which goods are declared for Customs import procedure based on the 1999 Kyoto Convention.

values.label: Previous transport document
values.comment: Identification of the previous transport document.

values.label: Insurance certificate
values.comment: Document/message issued to the insured certifying that insurance has been effected and that a policy has been issued. Such a certificate for a particular cargo is primarily used when good are insured under the terms of a floating or an open policy; at the request of the insured it can be exchanged for a policy.

values.label: Special requirements permit related to the transport of cargo
values.comment: A permit related to a transport document granting the transport of cargo under the conditions as specifically required.

values.label: Dangerous Goods Notification for Tanker vessel
values.comment: Dangerous Goods Notification for a vessel carrying liquid cargo in bulk.

values.label: Dangerous Goods Notification for non-tanker vessel
values.comment: Dangerous Goods Notification for a vessel carrying cargo other than bulk liquid cargo.

values.label: WCO Conveyance Arrival Report
values.comment: Declaration, in accordance with the WCO Customs Data Model, to Customs regarding the conveyance arriving in a Customs territory.

values.label: WCO Conveyance Departure Report
values.comment: Declaration, in accordance with the WCO Customs Data Model, to Customs regarding the conveyance departing a Customs territory.

values.label: Accounting voucher
values.comment: A document/message justifying an accounting entry.

values.label: Self billed debit note
values.comment: A document which indicates that the customer is claiming debit in a self billing environment.

values.label: Military Identification Card
values.comment: The official document used for military personnel on travel orders, substituting a passport.

values.label: Re-Entry Permit
values.comment: A permit to re-enter a country.

values.label: Insurance policy
values.comment: Document/message issued by the insurer evidencing an agreement to insure and containing the conditions of the agreement concluded whereby the insurer undertakes for a specific fee to indemnify the insured for the losses arising out of the perils and accidents specified in the contract.

values.label: Refugee Permit
values.comment: Document identifying a refugee recognized by a country.

values.label: Forwarders credit note
values.comment: Document/message for providing credit information to the relevant party.

values.label: Original accounting voucher
values.comment: To indicate that the document/message justifying an accounting entry is original.

values.label: Copy accounting voucher
values.comment: To indicate that the document/message justifying an accounting entry is a copy.

values.label: Pro-forma accounting voucher
values.comment: To indicate that the document/message justifying an accounting entry is pro-forma.

values.label: International Ship Security Certificate
values.comment: A certificate on ship security issued based on the International code for the Security of Ships and of Port facilities (ISPS code).

values.label: Interim International Ship Security Certificate
values.comment: An interim certificate on ship security issued basis under the International code for the Security of Ships and of Port facilities (ISPS code).

values.label: Good Manufacturing Practice (GMP) Certificate
values.comment: Certificate that guarantees quality manufacturing and processing of food products, medications, cosmetics, etc.

values.label: Framework Agreement
values.comment: An agreement between one or more contracting authorities and one or more economic operators, the purpose of which is to establish the terms governing contracts to be awarded during a given period, in particular with regard to price and, where appropriate, the quantity envisaged.

values.label: Insurance declaration sheet (bordereau)
values.comment: A document/message used when an insured reports to his insurer details of individual shipments which are covered by an insurance contract - an open cover or a floating policy - between the parties.

values.label: Transport capacity offer
values.comment: Offering of capacity for the transport of goods for a date and a route.

values.label: Ship Security Plan
values.comment: Ship Security Plan (SSP) is a document prepared in terms of the ISPS Code to contribute to the prevention of illegal acts against the ship and its crew.

values.label: Forwarders invoice discrepancy report
values.comment: Document/message reporting invoice discrepancies indentified by the forwarder.

values.label: Storage capacity offer
values.comment: Offering of capacity to store goods.

values.label: Insurer's invoice
values.comment: Document/message issued by an insurer specifying the cost of an insurance which has been effected and claiming payment therefore.

values.label: Storage capacity request
values.comment: Request for capacity to store goods.

values.label: Transport capacity request
values.comment: Request for capacity for the transport of goods for a date and a route.

values.label: EU Customs declaration for External Community Transit (T1)
values.comment: Customs declaration for goods under the external Community/common transit procedure. This applies to "non-Community goods" ("T1" under EU legislation and EC- EFTA "Transit Convention").

values.label: EU Customs declaration for internal Community Transit (T2)
values.comment: Customs declaration for goods under the internal Community/common transit procedure. This applies to "Community goods" ("T2" under EU legislation and EC-EFTA "Transit Convention").

values.label: Cover note
values.comment: Document/message issued by an insurer (insurance broker, agent, etc.) to notify the insured that his insurance have been carried out.

values.label: EU Customs declaration for non-fiscal area internal Community Transit (T2F)
values.comment: Declaration for goods under the internal Community transit procedure in the context of trade between the "VAT" territory of EU Member States and EU territories where the VAT rules do not apply, such as Canary islands, some French overseas territories, the Channel islands and the Aaland islands, and between those territories. ("T2F" under EU Legislation).

values.label: EU Customs declaration for internal transit to San Marino (T2SM)
values.comment: Customs declaration for goods under the internal Community transit procedure between the Community and San Marino. ("T2SM" under EU Legislation).

values.label: EU Customs declaration for mixed consignments (T)
values.comment: Customs declaration for goods under the Community/common transit procedure for mixed consignments (i.e. consignments that comprise goods of different statuses, like "T1" and "T2") ("T" under EU Legislation).

values.label: EU Document for establishing the Community status of goods (T2L)
values.comment: Form establishing the Community status of goods ("T2L" under EU Legislation).

values.label: EU Document for establishing the Community status of goods for certain fiscal purposes (T2LF)
values.comment: Form establishing the Community status of goods in the context of trade between the "VAT" territory of EU Member States and EU territories where the VAT rules do not apply, such as Canary islands, some French overseas territories, the Channel islands and the Aaland islands, and between those territories ("T2LF" under EU Legislation).

values.label: Document for establishing the Customs Status of goods for San Marino (T2LSM)
values.comment: Form establishing the Community status of goods ("T2L" under European Legislation) in the context of trade between the EU and San Marino. ("T2LSM" under EU Legislation).

values.label: Customs declaration for TIR Carnet goods
values.comment: A Customs declaration in which goods move under cover of TIR Carnets.

values.label: Transport Means Security Report
values.comment: A document reporting the security status and related information of a means of transport.

values.label: Halal Slaughtering Certificate
values.comment: A certificate verifying that meat has been produced from slaughter in accordance with Islamic laws and practices.

values.label: Forwarding instructions
values.comment: Document/message issued to a freight forwarder, giving instructions regarding the action to be taken by the forwarder for the forwarding of goods described therein.

values.label: Forwarder's advice to import agent
values.comment: Document/message issued by a freight forwarder in an exporting country advising his counterpart in an importing country about the forwarding of goods described therein.

values.label: Forwarder's advice to exporter
values.comment: Document/message issued by a freight forwarder informing an exporter of the action taken in fulfillment of instructions received.

values.label: Forwarder's invoice
values.comment: Invoice issued by a freight forwarder specifying services rendered and costs incurred and claiming payment therefore.

values.label: Forwarder's certificate of receipt
values.comment: Non-negotiable document issued by a forwarder to certify that he has assumed control of a specified consignment, with irrevocable instructions to send it to the consignee indicated in the document or to hold it at his disposal. E.g. FIATA-FCR.

values.label: Heat Treatment Certificate
values.comment: A certificate verifying the heat treatment of the product is in conformance with international standards to ensure the products healthiness and/or shows the mode of heat treatment indicating the temperature and the amount of time the product or raw material used in the product was treated (such as milk).

values.label: Convention on International Trade in Endangered Species of Wild Fauna and Flora (CITES) Certificate
values.comment: A certificate used in the trade of endangered species in accordance with the CITES convention.

values.label: Free Sale Certificate in the Country of Origin
values.comment: A certificate confirming that a specified product is free for sale in the country of origin.

values.label: Transit license
values.comment: Document/message issued by the competent body in accordance with transit regulations in force, by which authorization is granted to a party to move articles under customs procedure.

values.label: Veterinary quarantine certificate
values.comment: A certification that livestock or animal products, that are either imported or entering free zones, are kept under health supervision for a time period determined by veterinary quarantine instructions.

values.label: Shipping note
values.comment: (1123) Document/message provided by the shipper or his agent to the carrier, multimodal transport operator, terminal or other receiving authority, giving information about export consignments offered for transport, and providing for the necessary receipts and declarations of liability. Sometimes a multipurpose cargo handling document also fulfilling the functions of document 632, 633, 650 and 655.

values.label: Forwarder's warehouse receipt
values.comment: Document/message issued by a forwarder acting as Warehouse Keeper acknowledging receipt of goods placed in a warehouse, and stating or referring to the conditions which govern the warehousing and the release of goods. The document contains detailed provisions regarding the rights of holders-by-endorsement, transfer of ownership, etc. E.g. FIATA-FWR.

values.label: Goods receipt
values.comment: Document/message to acknowledge the receipt of goods and in addition may indicate receiving conditions.

values.label: Port charges documents
values.comment: Documents/messages specifying services rendered, storage and handling costs, demurrage and other charges due to the owner of goods described therein.

values.label: Certified list of ingredients
values.comment: A document legalized from a competent authority that shows the components of the product (food additive, detergent, disinfectant and sanitizer).

values.label: Warehouse warrant
values.comment: Negotiable receipt document, issued by a Warehouse Keeper to a person placing goods in a warehouse and conferring title to the goods stored.

values.label: Health certificate
values.comment: A document legalized from a competent authority that shows that the product has been tested microbiologically and is free from any pathogens and fit for human consumption and/or declares that the product is in compliance with sanitary and phytosanitary measures.

values.label: Food grade certificate
values.comment: A document that shows that the product (food additive, detergent, disinfectant and sanitizer) is suitable to be used in the food industry.

values.label: Certificate of suitability for transport of grains and legumes
values.comment: Certificate of inspection for the vessel stating its readiness and suitability for transporting grains and legumes.

values.label: Certificate of refrigerated transport equipment inspection
values.comment: Inspection document shows that the container, the cooling devices and measured temperature is in good working condition.

values.label: Delivery order
values.comment: Document/message issued by a party entitled to authorize the release of goods specified therein to a named consignee, to be retained by the custodian of the goods.

values.label: Thermographic reading report
values.comment: A report of temperature readings over a period.

values.label: Certificate of food item transport readiness
values.comment: A certificate to verify readiness of a transport or transport area such as a reservoir or hold to transport food items.

values.label: Food packaging contact certificate
values.comment: A document legalized from a competent authority that shows that the food packaging product is safe to come into contact with food.

values.label: Packaging material composition report
values.comment: A document that shows the main structure that composes the packaging material.

values.label: Export price certificate
values.comment: A certification executed by the competent authority from country of exportation stating the export price of the goods.

values.label: Public price certificate
values.comment: A certification executed by the competent authority from country of production stating the price of the goods to the general public.

values.label: Drug shelf life study report
values.comment: A document containing results from the study which determines the shelf life, namely the time period of storage at a specified condition within which a drug substance or drug product still meets its established specifications; its identity, strength, quality and purity.

values.label: Certificate of compliance with standards of the World Organization for Animal Health (OIE)
values.comment: A certification that the products have been treated in a way consistent with the standards set by the World Organization for Animal Health (OIE).

values.label: Production facility license
values.comment: A license granted by a competent authority to a production facility for manufacturing specific products.

values.label: Handling order
values.comment: Document/message issued by a cargo handling organization (port administration, terminal operator, etc.) for the removal or other handling of goods under their care.

values.label: Manufacturing license
values.comment: A license granted by a competent authority to a manufacturer for production of specific products.

values.label: Low risk country formal letter
values.comment: An official letter issued by an import authority granted to the importer of goods from a low risk country which allows the importer to place its products in the local market with certain favorable considerations.

values.label: Previous correspondence
values.comment: Correspondence previously exchanged.

values.label: Declaration for radioactive material
values.comment: A declaration to be presented to the competent authority when radioactive material moves cross-border.

values.label: Gate pass
values.comment: Document/message authorizing goods specified therein to be brought out of a fenced-in port or terminal area.

values.label: Resale information
values.comment: Document/message providing information on a resale.

values.label: Phytosanitary Re-export Certificate
values.comment: A message/document consistent with the model for re- export phytosanitary certificates of the IPPC, attesting that a consignment meets phytosanitary import requirements.

values.label: Bayplan/stowage plan, full
values.comment: A full bayplan containing all occupied and/or blocked stowage locations.

values.label: Bayplan/stowage plan, partial
values.comment: A partial bayplan. containing only a selected part of the available stowage locations.

values.label: Waybill
values.comment: Non-negotiable document evidencing the contract for the transport of cargo.

values.label: Universal (multipurpose) transport document
values.comment: Document/message evidencing a contract of carriage covering the movement of goods by any mode of transport, or combination of modes, for national as well as international transport, under any applicable international convention or national law and under the conditions of carriage of any carrier or transport operator undertaking or arranging the transport referred to in the document.

values.label: Goods receipt, carriage
values.comment: Document/message issued by a carrier or a carrier's agent, acknowledging receipt for carriage of goods specified therein on conditions stated or referred to in the document, enabling the carrier to issue a transport document.

values.label: House waybill
values.comment: The document made out by an agent/consolidator which evidences the contract between the shipper and the agent/consolidator for the arrangement of carriage of goods.

values.label: Master bill of lading
values.comment: A bill of lading issued by the master of a vessel (in actuality the owner or charterer of the vessel). It could cover a number of house bills.

values.label: Bill of lading
values.comment: Negotiable document/message which evidences a contract of carriage by sea and the taking over or loading of goods by carrier, and by which carrier undertakes to deliver goods against surrender of the document. A provision in the document that goods are to be delivered to the order of a named person, or to order, or to bearer, constitutes such an undertaking.

values.label: Bill of lading original
values.comment: The original of the bill of lading issued by a transport company. When issued by the maritime industry it could signify ownership of the cargo.

values.label: Bill of lading copy
values.comment: A copy of the bill of lading issued by a transport company.

values.label: Empty container bill
values.comment: Bill of lading indicating an empty container.

values.label: Tanker bill of lading
values.comment: Document which evidences a transport of liquid bulk cargo.

values.label: Sea waybill
values.comment: Non-negotiable document which evidences a contract for the carriage of goods by sea and the taking over of the goods by the carrier, and by which the carrier undertakes to deliver the goods to the consignee named in the document.

values.label: Inland waterway bill of lading
values.comment: Negotiable transport document made out to a named person, to order or to bearer, signed by the carrier and handed to the sender after receipt of the goods.

values.label: Non-negotiable maritime transport document (generic)
values.comment: Non-negotiable document which evidences a contract for the carriage of goods by sea and the taking over or loading of the goods by the carrier, and by which the carrier undertakes to deliver the goods to the consignee named in the document. E.g. Sea waybill. Remark: Synonymous with "straight" or "non-negotiable Bill of lading" used in certain countries, e.g. Canada.

values.label: Mate's receipt
values.comment: Document/message issued by a ship's officer to acknowledge that a specified consignment has been received on board a vessel, and the apparent condition of the goods; enabling the carrier to issue a Bill of lading.

values.label: House bill of lading
values.comment: The bill of lading issued not by the carrier but by the freight forwarder/consolidator known by the carrier.

values.label: Letter of indemnity for non-surrender of bill of lading
values.comment: Document/message issued by a commercial party or a bank of an insurance company accepting responsibility to the beneficiary of the indemnity in accordance with the terms thereof.

values.label: Forwarder's bill of lading
values.comment: Non-negotiable document issued by a freight forwarder evidencing a contract for the carriage of goods by sea and the taking over or loading of the goods by the freight forwarder, and by which the freight forwarder undertakes to deliver the goods to the consignee named in the document.

values.label: Residence permit
values.comment: A document authorizing residence.

values.label: Seamans book
values.comment: A national identity document issued to professional seamen that contains a record of their rank and service career.

values.label: General message
values.comment: Document/message providing agreed textual information.

values.label: Rail consignment note (generic term)
values.comment: Transport document constituting a contract for the carriage of goods between the sender and the carrier (the railway). For international rail traffic, this document must conform to the model prescribed by the international conventions concerning carriage of goods by rail, e.g. CIM Convention, SMGS Convention.

values.label: Product data response
values.comment: Document/message responding to a previously received Product Data document/message.

values.label: Road list-SMGS
values.comment: Accounting document, one copy of which is drawn up for each consignment note; it accompanies the consignment over the whole route and is a rail transport document.

values.label: Escort official recognition
values.comment: Document/message which gives right to the owner to exert all functions normally transferred to a guard in a train by which an escorted consignment is transported.

values.label: Recharging document
values.comment: Fictitious transport document regarding a previous transport, enabling a carrier's agent to give to another carrier's agent (in a different country) the possibility to collect charges relating to the original transport (rail environment).

values.label: Manufacturer raised order
values.comment: Document/message providing details of an order which has been raised by a manufacturer.

values.label: Manufacturer raised consignment order
values.comment: Document/message providing details of a consignment order which has been raised by a manufacturer.

values.label: Price/sales catalogue not containing commercial information
values.comment: A price/sales catalogue message containing no commercial information, such as prices, terms or conditions.

values.label: Price/sales catalogue containing commercial information
values.comment: A price/sales catalogue message containing only commercial terms or conditions data.

values.label: Returns advice
values.comment: Document/message by means of which the buyer informs the seller about the despatch of returned goods.

values.label: Road consignment note
values.comment: Transport document/message which evidences a contract between a carrier and a sender for the carriage of goods by road (generic term). Remark: For international road traffic, this document must contain at least the particulars prescribed by the convention on the contract for the international carriage of goods by road (CMR).

values.label: Commercial account summary
values.comment: A message enabling the transmission of commercial data concerning payments made and outstanding items on an account over a period of time.

values.label: Announcement for returns
values.comment: A message by which a party announces to another party details of goods for return due to specified reasons (e.g. returns for repair, returns because of damage, etc).

values.label: Instruction for returns
values.comment: A message by which a party informs another party whether and how goods shall be returned.

values.label: Sales forecast report
values.comment: A message enabling companies to exchange or report electronically, basic sales forecast data related to products or services, including the corresponding location, time period, product identification, pricing and quantity information. It enables the recip.

values.label: Sales data report
values.comment: A message enabling companies to exchange or report electronically, basic sales data related to products or services, including the corresponding location, time period, product identification, pricing and quantity information. It enables the recipient to p.

values.label: Standing inquiry on complete product information
values.comment: A product inquiry which stands until it is cancelled. It requests not only the updates since last time, but always the complete product information of a data supplier. This means that within the standing request every time a complete download of the respe.

values.label: Proof of delivery
values.comment: A message by which a consignee provides for a carrier proof of delivery of a consignment.

values.label: Cargo/goods handling and movement message
values.comment: A message from a party to a warehouse, distribution centre, or logistics service provider identifying the handling services and where required the movement of specified goods, limited to warehouses within the jurisdiction of the distribution centre or log.

values.label: Metered services consumption report supporting an invoice
values.comment: Document/message providing metered consumption details supporiting an invoice.

values.label: Air waybill
values.comment: Document/message made out by or on behalf of the shipper which evidences the contract between the shipper and carrier(s) for carriage of goods over routes of the carrier(s) and which is identified by the airline prefix issuing the document plus a serial (IATA).

values.label: Master air waybill
values.comment: Document/message made out by or on behalf of the agent/consolidator which evidences the contract between the agent/consolidator and carrier(s) for carriage of goods over routes of the carrier(s) for a consignment consisting of goods originated by more than one shipper (IATA).

values.label: Metered services consumption report
values.comment: Document/message providing metered consumption details.

values.label: Substitute air waybill
values.comment: A temporary air waybill which contains only limited information because of the absence of the original.

values.label: Crew's effects declaration
values.comment: Declaration to Customs regarding the personal effects of crew members aboard the conveyance; equivalent to IMO FAL 4.

values.label: Passenger list
values.comment: Declaration to Customs regarding passengers aboard the conveyance; equivalent to IMO FAL 6.

values.label: Delivery notice (rail transport)
values.comment: Document/message created by the consignor or by the departure station, joined to the transport or sent to the consignee, giving the possibility to the consignee or the arrival station to attest the delivery of the goods. The document must be returned to the consignor or to the departure station.

values.label: Payroll deductions advice
values.comment: A message sent by a party (usually an employer or its representative) to a service providing organisation, to detail payroll deductions paid on behalf of its employees to the service providing organisation.

values.label: Consignment despatch advice
values.comment: Document/message by means of which the supplier informs the buyer about the despatch of goods ordered on consignment (goods to be delivered into stock with agreement on payment when goods are sold out of this stock).

values.label: Transport equipment gross mass verification message
values.comment: Message containing information regarding gross mass verification of transport equipment.

values.label: Despatch note (post parcels)
values.comment: Document/message which, according to Article 106 of the "Agreement concerning Postal Parcels" under the UPU convention, is to accompany post parcels.

values.label: Invoice information for accounting purposes
values.comment: A document / message containing accounting related information such as monetary summations, seller id and VAT information. This may not be a complete invoice according to legal requirements. For instance the line item information might be excluded.

values.label: Plant Passport
values.comment: Document/message issued by a competent body certifying the phytosanitary status of plants or plant products for international trade.

values.label: Certificate of sustainability
values.comment: Document/message issued by a competent body certifying sustainability.

values.label: Call for tender
values.comment: A document/message used by a buyer to define the procurement procedure and request suppliers to participate.

values.label: Invitation to tender
values.comment: A document/message used by a buyer to define the procurement procedure and request specific suppliers to participate.

values.label: European Single Procurement Document request
values.comment: A document/message requesting a self-declaration from the supplier, providing preliminary evidence during the tendering phase.

values.label: Tendering price/sales catalogue request
values.comment: A document/message requesting information regarding pricing and catalogue details for goods and/or services to be offered as part of a tender.

values.label: Tender
values.comment: A document/message used by a supplier to bid in a procurement procedure.

values.label: European Single Procurement Document
values.comment: A document/message containing a self-declaration by the supplier, providing preliminary evidence during the tendering phase.

values.label: Multimodal/combined transport document (generic)
values.comment: A transport document used when more than one mode of transportation is involved in the movement of cargo. It is a contract of carriage and receipt of the cargo for a multimodal transport. It indicates the place where the responsible transport company in the move takes responsibility for the cargo, the place where the responsibility of this transport company in the move ends and the conveyances involved.

values.label: Through bill of lading
values.comment: Bill of lading which evidences a contract of carriage from one place to another in separate stages of which at least one stage is a sea transit, and by which the issuing carrier accepts responsibility for the carriage as set forth in the through bill of lading.

values.label: Tendering price/sales catalogue
values.comment: A document/message providing information regarding pricing and catalogue details for goods and/or services to be offered as part of a tender.

values.label: Forwarder's certificate of transport
values.comment: Negotiable document/message issued by a forwarder to certify that he has taken charge of a specified consignment for despatch and delivery in accordance with the consignor's instructions, as indicated in the document, and that he accepts responsibility for delivery of the goods to the holder of the document through the intermediary of a delivery agent of his choice. E.g. FIATA-FCT.

values.label: Combined transport document (generic)
values.comment: Negotiable or non-negotiable document evidencing a contract for the performance and/or procurement of performance of combined transport of goods and bearing on its face either the heading "Negotiable combined transport document issued subject to Uniform Rules for a Combined Transport Document (ICC Brochure No. 298)" or the heading "Non-negotiable Combined Transport Document issued subject to Uniform Rules for a Combined Transport Document (ICC Brochure No. 298)".

values.label: Multimodal transport document (generic)
values.comment: Document/message which evidences a multimodal transport contract, the taking in charge of the goods by the multimodal transport operator, and an undertaking by him to deliver the goods in accordance with the terms of the contract. (International Convention on Multimodal Transport of Goods).

values.label: Combined transport bill of lading/multimodal bill of lading
values.comment: Document which evidences a multimodal transport contract, the taking in charge of the goods by the multimodal transport operator, and an undertaking by him to deliver the goods in accordance with the terms of the contract.

values.label: Acknowledgment of receipt
values.comment: Document/message confirming a receipt to the sending party.

values.label: Civil status document
values.comment: Document which confirms the civil status of a person.

values.label: Advice report
values.comment: Document reporting advice.

values.label: Booking confirmation
values.comment: Document/message issued by a carrier to confirm that space has been reserved for a consignment in means of transport.

values.label: Binding offer
values.comment: Document which is a binding offer from one party to another.

values.label: Binding customer agreement for contract
values.comment: Document which is a binding agreement from the customer for a contract, such as an insurance contract.

values.label: Coverage confirmation note
values.comment: Document confirming that insurance coverage is granted.

values.label: General terms and conditions
values.comment: Document specifying general terms and conditions.

values.label: Calling forward notice
values.comment: Instructions for release or delivery of goods.

values.label: Contract clauses
values.comment: Document specifying the clauses applying to a contract.

values.label: Specific contract conditions
values.comment: Document specifying the individual conditions or clauses applying to a specific contract.

values.label: Group insurance rules
values.comment: Document stating the rules of a group insurance contract.

values.label: Questionnaire
values.comment: Document consisting of a series of questions.

values.label: Freight invoice
values.comment: Document/message issued by a transport operation specifying freight costs and charges incurred for a transport operation and stating conditions of payment.

values.label: Arrival notice (goods)
values.comment: Notification from the carrier to the consignee in writing, by telephone or by any other means (express letter, message, telegram, etc.) informing him that a consignment addressed to him is being or will shortly be held at his disposal at a specified point in the place of destination.

values.label: Notice of circumstances preventing delivery (goods)
values.comment: Request made by the carrier to the sender, or, as the case may be, the consignee, for instructions as to the disposal of the consignment when circumstances prevent delivery and the return of the goods has not been requested by the consignor in the transport document.

values.label: Notice of circumstances preventing transport (goods)
values.comment: Request made by the carrier to the sender, or, the consignee as the case may be, for instructions as to the disposal of the goods when circumstances prevent transport before departure or en route, after acceptance of the consignment concerned.

values.label: Delivery notice (goods)
values.comment: Notification in writing, sent by the carrier to the sender, to inform him at his request of the actual date of delivery of the goods.

values.label: Cargo manifest
values.comment: Listing of goods comprising the cargo carried in a means of transport or in a transport-unit. The cargo manifest gives the commercial particulars of the goods, such as transport document numbers, consignors, consignees, shipping marks, number and kind of packages and descriptions and quantities of the goods.

values.label: Freight manifest
values.comment: Document/message containing the same information as a cargo manifest, and additional details on freight amounts, charges, etc.

values.label: Bordereau
values.comment: Document/message used in road transport, listing the cargo carried on a road vehicle, often referring to appended copies of Road consignment note.

values.label: Container manifest (unit packing list)
values.comment: Document/message specifying the contents of particular freight containers or other transport units, prepared by the party responsible for their loading into the container or unit.

values.label: Charges note
values.comment: Document used by the rail organization to indicate freight charges or additional charges in each case where the departure station is not able to calculate the charges for the total voyage (e.g. tariff not yet updated, part of voyage not covered by the tariff). This document must be considered as joined to the transport.

values.label: Advice of collection
values.comment: (1030) Document that is joined to the transport or sent by separate means, giving to the departure rail organization the proof that the cash-on delivery amount has been encashed by the arrival rail organization before reimbursement of the consignor.

values.label: Safety of ship certificate
values.comment: Document certifying a ship's safety to a specified date.

values.label: Safety of radio certificate
values.comment: Document certifying the safety of a ship's radio facilities to a specified date.

values.label: Safety of equipment certificate
values.comment: Document certifying the safety of a ship's equipment to a specified date.

values.label: Civil liability for oil certificate
values.comment: Document declaring a ship owner's liability for oil propelling or carried on a vessel.

values.label: Loadline document
values.comment: Document specifying the limit of a ship's legal submersion under various conditions.

values.label: Derat document
values.comment: Document certifying that a ship is free of rats, valid to a specified date.

values.label: Maritime declaration of health
values.comment: Document certifying the health condition on board a vessel, valid to a specified date.

values.label: Certificate of registry
values.comment: Official certificate stating the vessel's registry.

values.label: Ship's stores declaration
values.comment: Declaration to Customs regarding the contents of the ship's stores (equivalent to IMO FAL 3) i.e. goods intended for consumption by passengers/crew on board vessels, aircraft or trains, whether or not sold or landed; goods necessary for operation/maintenance of conveyance, including fuel/lubricants, excluding spare parts/equipment (IMO).

values.label: Export licence, application for
values.comment: Application for a permit issued by a government authority permitting exportation of a specified commodity subject to specified conditions as quantity, country of destination, etc.

values.label: Export licence
values.comment: Permit issued by a government authority permitting exportation of a specified commodity subject to specified conditions as quantity, country of destination, etc. Synonym: Embargo permit.

values.label: Exchange control declaration, export
values.comment: Document/message completed by an exporter/seller as a means whereby the competent body may control that the amount of foreign exchange accrued from a trade transaction is repatriated in accordance with the conditions of payment and exchange control regulations in force.

values.label: Declaration of final beneficiary
values.comment: Declaration document to identify the final beneficiary of an asset.

values.label: US, FATCA statement
values.comment: Statement regarding the Foreign Account Tax Compliance Act (FATCA) of the United States of America.

values.label: Insured status report
values.comment: Document reporting (e.g. annually) to the insured the actual details of an insurance contract.

values.label: Group pension commitment information
values.comment: Information document for the group pension commitment to an individual person.

values.label: Claim notification
values.comment: Document notifying a claim.

values.label: Assessment report
values.comment: Document reporting an assessment.

values.label: Loss statement
values.comment: Document specifying the value of a loss.

values.label: Despatch note model T
values.comment: European community transit declaration.

values.label: Despatch note model T1
values.comment: Transit declaration for goods circulating under internal community transit procedures (between European Union (EU) countries).

values.label: Despatch note model T2
values.comment: Ascertainment that the declared goods were originally produced in an European Union (EU) country.

values.label: Control document T5
values.comment: Control document (export declaration) used particularly in case of re-sending without use with only VAT collection, refusal, unconformity with contract etc.

values.label: Re-sending consignment note
values.comment: Rail consignment note prepared by the consignor for the facilitation of an eventual return to the origin of the goods.

values.label: Despatch note model T2L
values.comment: Ascertainment that the declared goods were originally produced in an European Union (EU) country. May only be used for goods that are loaded on one single means of transport in one single departure point for one single delivery point.

values.label: Guarantee of cost acceptance
values.comment: Document certifying the guarantee of the document issuer that he will pay for costs of the addressee, e.g. the costs for repairing a vehicle.

values.label: Close of claim
values.comment: Document reporting the closing of a claim file.

values.label: Refusal of claim
values.comment: Document stating the refusal of a claim.

values.label: Valuation report
values.comment: Document reporting a valuation.

values.label: Goods declaration for exportation
values.comment: Document/message by which goods are declared for export Customs clearance, conforming to the layout key set out at Appendix I to Annex C.1 concerning outright exportation to the Kyoto convention (CCC). Within a Customs union, "for despatch" may have the same meaning as "for exportation".

values.label: Claim history certificate
values.comment: Document which certifies the history of claims.

values.label: Accounting statement
values.comment: Document specifying an accounting statement.

values.label: Cargo declaration (departure)
values.comment: Generic term, sometimes referred to as Freight declaration, applied to the documents providing the particulars required by the Customs concerning the cargo (freight) carried by commercial means of transport (CCC).

values.label: Payment receipt confirmation
values.comment: Document confirming the receipt of a payment.

values.label: Certificate of paid insurance premium
values.comment: Document certifying the payment of the insurance premium.

values.label: Insured party payment report
values.comment: Report about payments done towards an insured party.

values.label: Third party payment report
values.comment: Report about payments done towards a third party.

values.label: Direct debit authorisation
values.comment: Document giving the addressee the right to debit from an account of the authorizing party.

values.label: Physician report
values.comment: Report issued by a medical doctor.

values.label: Application for goods control certificate
values.comment: Document/message submitted to a competent body by party requesting a Goods control certificate to be issued in accordance with national or international standards, or conforming to legislation in the importing country, or as specified in the contract.

values.label: Goods control certificate
values.comment: Document/message issued by a competent body evidencing the quality of the goods described therein, in accordance with national or international standards, or conforming to legislation in the importing country, or as specified in the contract.

values.label: Medical certificate
values.comment: Document certifying a medical condition.

values.label: Witness report
values.comment: Document containing a report of a witness.

values.label: Calculation note
values.comment: Document detailing a calculation, such as an invoice calculation or a costs calculation.

values.label: Communication from opposite party
values.comment: Document containing a communication from the opposite party, such as in legal action.

values.label: Amicable agreement
values.comment: Document specifying an amicable agreement.

values.label: Out of court settlement
values.comment: Document which specifies an out of court settlement.

values.label: Legal action
values.comment: Document specifying a legal action at court.

values.label: Summons
values.comment: Document specifying a summons to court.

values.label: Application for phytosanitary certificate
values.comment: Document/message submitted to a competent body by party requesting a Phytosanitary certificate to be issued.

values.label: Phytosanitary certificate
values.comment: A message/doucment consistent with the model for certificates of the IPPC, attesting that a consignment meets phytosanitary import requirements.

values.label: Sanitary certificate
values.comment: Document/message issued by the competent authority in the exporting country evidencing that alimentary and animal products, including dead animals, are fit for human consumption, and giving details, when relevant, of controls undertaken.

values.label: Veterinary certificate
values.comment: Document/message issued by the competent authority in the exporting country evidencing that live animals or birds are not infested or infected with disease, and giving details regarding their provenance, and of vaccinations and other treatment to which they have been subjected.

values.label: Court judgment
values.comment: Document specifying a judgment of a court.

values.label: Application for inspection certificate
values.comment: Document/message submitted to a competent body by a party requesting an Inspection certificate to be issued in accordance with national or international standards, or conforming to legislation in the country in which it is required, or as specified in the contract.

values.label: Inspection certificate
values.comment: Document/message issued by a competent body evidencing that the goods described therein have been inspected in accordance with national or international standards, in conformity with legislation in the country in which the inspection is required, or as specified in the contract.

values.label: Vehicle aboard document
values.comment: Document which must be aboard the vehicle.

values.label: Image
values.comment: Document consisting of an image.

values.label: Audio
values.comment: Document consisting of an audio recording (e.g. a telephone conversation or alike).

values.label: Certificate of origin, application for
values.comment: Document/message submitted to a competent body by an interested party requesting a Certificate of origin to be issued in accordance with relevant criteria, and on the basis of evidence of the origin of the goods.

values.label: Certificate of origin
values.comment: Document/message identifying goods, in which the authority or body authorized to issue it certifies expressly that the goods to which the certificate relates originate in a specific country. The word "country" may include a group of countries, a region or a part of a country. This certificate may also include a declaration by the manufacturer, producer, supplier, exporter or other competent person.

values.label: Declaration of origin
values.comment: Appropriate statement as to the origin of the goods, made in connection with their exportation by the manufacturer, producer, supplier, exporter or other competent person on the Commercial invoice or any other document relating to the goods (CCC).

values.label: Regional appellation certificate
values.comment: Certificate drawn up in accordance with the rules laid down by an authority or approved body, certifying that the goods described therein qualify for a designation specific to the given region (e.g. champagne, port wine, Parmesan cheese).

values.label: Preference certificate of origin
values.comment: Document/message describing a certificate of origin meeting the requirements for preferential treatment.

values.label: Certificate of origin form GSP
values.comment: Specific form of certificate of origin for goods qualifying for preferential treatment under the generalized system of preferences (includes a combined declaration of origin and certificate, form A).

values.label: Video
values.comment: Document consisting of a video.

values.label: Introductory letter
values.comment: A letter of introduction attached to, or accompanying another document such as an insurance policy.

values.label: Data protection regulations statement
values.comment: Document specifying the terms of data protection regulations.

values.label: Exclusive brokerage mandate
values.comment: Document expressing the mandate of a client for a service only by the mandated broker.

values.label: Consular invoice
values.comment: Document/message to be prepared by an exporter in his country and presented to a diplomatic representation of the importing country for endorsement and subsequently to be presented by the importer in connection with the import of the goods described therein.

values.label: Inquiry mandate
values.comment: Document expressing the mandate of a client for an inquiry service by the mandated provider.

values.label: Risk analysis
values.comment: Document specifying the analysis of risks.

values.label: Transport equipment movement report, partial
values.comment: A partial transport equipment movement report, containing only a selected part of the movements of transport equipment for a vessel in a port.

values.label: Conveyance declaration
values.comment: Declaration of the conveyance to a public authority.

values.label: Partial construction invoice
values.comment: Partial invoice in the context of a specific construction project.

values.label: Partial final construction invoice
values.comment: Invoice concluding all previous partial construction invoices of a completed partial rendered service in the context of a specific construction project.

values.label: Final construction invoice
values.comment: Invoice concluding all previous partial invoices and partial final construction invoices in the context of a specific construction project.

values.label: AEO Certificate of Security and/or Safety
values.comment: Certificate issued to business that fulfils specified criteria applied to the security and safety of the logistics chain in the flow of foreign trade operations by a national AEO recognized program (e.g. AEO-Security and Safety (AEOS) - Regulation (EU) No 952/2013).

values.label: AEO Certificate of Conformity or Compliance
values.comment: Certificate issued to business that fulfils specified criteria for compliance with tax and customs obligations, as well as financial solvency by a national AEO recognized program (e.g. AEO-Customs Simplifications (AEOC) - Regulation (EU) No 952/2013).

values.label: Dangerous goods declaration
values.comment: (1115) Document/message issued by a consignor in accordance with applicable conventions or regulations, describing hazardous goods or materials for transport purposes, and stating that the latter have been packed and labelled in accordance with the provisions of the relevant conventions or regulations.

values.label: AEO Certificate Full
values.comment: Certificate issued to business that fulfils specified criteria to both AEO Certificate of Security and/or Safety and AEO Certificate of Conformity or Compliance by a national AEO recognized program (e.g. AEO-Customs Simplifications/Security and Safety (AEOC/AEOS) - Regulation(EU) No 952/2013).

values.label: Purchase Order Financing Request
values.comment: Document enabling the Financing Requestor to initiate the financing process by the First Agent.

values.label: Purchase Order Financing Request Status
values.comment: Document enabling the First Agent to notify the Financing Requestor of the status of a purchase order financing request or the status of a purchase order financing cancellation request previously sent by the Financial Requestor itself.

values.label: Purchase Order Financing Request Cancellation
values.comment: Document enabling the Financing Requestor to request the First Agent to cancel a previously sent purchase order financing request.

values.label: Statistical document, export
values.comment: Document/message in which an exporter provides information about exported goods required by the body responsible for the collection of international trade statistics.

values.label: INTRASTAT declaration
values.comment: Document/message in which a declarant provides information about goods required by the body responsible for the collection of trade statistics.

values.label: Transit certificate of approval
values.comment: Certificate of approval for the transport of goods under customs seal

values.label: Pre-packed cross docking consignment order
values.comment: A consignment order requesting the supply of products packed according to the final delivery point which will be moved across a dock in a distribution centre without further handling.

values.label: Traceability event declaration
values.comment: Document/message declaring a traceability event.

values.label: Sustainability data request
values.comment: Document/message requesting information based on defined criteria regarding sustainability.

values.label: Delivery verification certificate
values.comment: Document/message whereby an official authority (Customs or governmental) certifies that goods have been delivered.

values.label: Sustainability data response
values.comment: Document/Message returned as an answer to a question regarding sustainability.

values.label: Sustainability Inspection request
values.comment: Document/message requesting a sustainability inspection.

values.label: Sustainability Inspection response
values.comment: Document/message reporting the results of a sustainability inspection.

values.label: Air Consignment Security Declaration
values.comment: Document/message issued by an air industry regulated agent as a means for the competent body to secure an audit trail of how, when and by whom cargo has been secured along the supply chain.

values.label: Import licence, application for
values.comment: Document/message in which an interested party applies to the competent body for authorization to import either a limited quantity of articles subject to import restrictions, or an unlimited quantity of such articles during a limited period, and specifies the kind of articles, their origin and value, etc.

values.label: Import licence
values.comment: Document/message issued by the competent body in accordance with import regulations in force, by which authorization is granted to a named party to import either a limited quantity of designated articles or an unlimited quantity of such articles during a limited period, under conditions specified in the document.

values.label: Customs declaration without commercial detail
values.comment: CUSDEC transmission that does not include data from the commercial detail section of the message.

values.label: Customs declaration with commercial and item detail
values.comment: CUSDEC transmission that includes data from both the commercial detail and item detail sections of the message.

values.label: Customs declaration without item detail
values.comment: CUSDEC transmission that does not include data from the item detail section of the message.

values.label: Related document
values.comment: Document that has a relationship with the stated document/message.

values.label: Receipt (Customs)
values.comment: Receipt for Customs duty/tax/fee paid.

values.label: Application for exchange allocation
values.comment: Document/message whereby an importer/buyer requests the competent body to allocate an amount of foreign exchange to be transferred to an exporter/seller in payment for goods.

values.label: Foreign exchange permit
values.comment: Document/message issued by the competent body authorizing an importer/buyer to transfer an amount of foreign exchange to an exporter/seller in payment for goods.

values.label: Exchange control declaration (import)
values.comment: Document/message completed by an importer/buyer as a means for the competent body to control that a trade transaction for which foreign exchange has been allocated has been executed and that money has been transferred in accordance with the conditions of payment and the exchange control regulations in force.

values.label: Goods declaration for importation
values.comment: Document/message by which goods are declared for import Customs clearance [sister entry of 830].

values.label: Goods declaration for home use
values.comment: Document/message by which goods are declared for import Customs clearance according to Annex B.1 (concerning clearance for home use) to the Kyoto convention (CCC).

values.label: Customs immediate release declaration
values.comment: Document/message issued by an importer notifying Customs that goods have been removed from an importing means of transport to the importer's premises under a Customs- approved arrangement for immediate release, or requesting authorization to do so.

values.label: Customs delivery note
values.comment: Document/message whereby a Customs authority releases goods under its control to be placed at the disposal of the party concerned. Synonym: Customs release note.

values.label: Cargo declaration (arrival)
values.comment: Generic term, sometimes referred to as Freight declaration, applied to the documents providing the particulars required by the Customs concerning the cargo (freight) carried by commercial means of transport (CCC).

values.label: Value declaration
values.comment: Document/message in which a declarant (importer) states the invoice or other price (e.g. selling price, price of identical goods), and specifies costs for freight, insurance and packing, etc., terms of delivery and payment, any relationship with the trading partner, etc., for the purpose of determining the Customs value of goods imported.

values.label: Customs invoice
values.comment: Document/message required by the Customs in an importing country in which an exporter states the invoice or other price (e.g. selling price, price of identical goods), and specifies costs for freight, insurance and packing, etc., terms of delivery and payment, for the purpose of determining the Customs value in the importing country of goods consigned to that country.

values.label: Customs declaration (post parcels)
values.comment: Document/message which, according to Article 106 of the "Agreement concerning Postal Parcels" under the UPU Convention, must accompany post parcels and in which the contents of such parcels are specified.

values.label: Tax declaration (value added tax)
values.comment: Document/message in which an importer states the pertinent information required by the competent body for assessment of value-added tax.

values.label: Tax declaration (general)
values.comment: Document/message containing a general tax declaration.

values.label: Tax demand
values.comment: Document/message containing the demand of tax.

values.label: Embargo permit
values.comment: Document/message giving the permission to export specified goods.

values.label: Goods declaration for Customs transit
values.comment: Document/message by which the sender declares goods for Customs transit according to Annex E.1 (concerning Customs transit) to the Kyoto convention (CCC).

values.label: TIF form
values.comment: International Customs transit document by which the sender declares goods for carriage by rail in accordance with the provisions of the 1952 International Convention to facilitate the crossing of frontiers for goods carried by rail (TIF Convention of UIC).

values.label: TIR carnet
values.comment: International Customs document (International Transit by Road), issued by a guaranteeing association approved by the Customs authorities, under the cover of which goods are carried, in most cases under Customs seal, in road vehicles and/or containers in compliance with the requirements of the Customs TIR Convention of the International Transport of Goods under cover of TIR Carnets (UN/ECE).

values.label: EC carnet
values.comment: EC customs transit document issued by EC customs authorities for transit and/or temporary user of goods within the EC.

values.label: EUR 1 certificate of origin
values.comment: Customs certificate used in preferential goods interchanges between EC countries and EC external countries.

values.label: ATA carnet
values.comment: International Customs document (Admission Temporaire / Temporary Admission) which, issued under the terms of the ATA Convention (1961), incorporates an internationally valid guarantee and may be used, in lieu of national Customs documents and as security for import duties and taxes, to cover the temporary admission of goods and, where appropriate, the transit of goods. If accepted for controlling the temporary export and reimport of goods, international guarantee does not apply (CCC).

values.label: Single administrative document
values.comment: A set of documents, replacing the various (national) forms for Customs declaration within the EC, implemented on 01-01-1988.

values.label: General response (Customs)
values.comment: General response message to permit the transfer of data from Customs to the transmitter of the previous message.

values.label: Document response (Customs)
values.comment: Document response message to permit the transfer of data from Customs to the transmitter of the previous message.

values.label: Error response (Customs)
values.comment: Error response message to permit the transfer of data from Customs to the transmitter of the previous message.

values.label: Package response (Customs)
values.comment: Package response message to permit the transfer of data from Customs to the transmitter of the previous message.

values.label: Tax calculation/confirmation response (Customs)
values.comment: Tax calculation/confirmation response message to permit the transfer of data from Customs to the transmitter of the previous message.

values.label: Quota prior allocation certificate
values.comment: Document/message issued by the competent body for prior allocation of a quota.

values.label: Wagon report
values.comment: Document which contains consignment information concerning the wagons and their lading in a case of a multiple wagon consignment.

values.label: Transit Conveyor Document
values.comment: Document for a course of transit used for a carrier who is neither the carrier at the beginning nor the arrival. The transit carrier can directly invoice the expenses for its part of the transport.

values.label: Rail consignment note forwarder copy
values.comment: Document which is a copy of the rail consignment note printed especially for the need of the forwarder.

values.label: Duty suspended goods
values.comment: Document giving details for the carriage of excisable goods on a duty-suspended basis.

values.label: Proof of transit declaration
values.comment: A document providing proof that a transit declaration has been accepted.

values.label: Container transfer note
values.comment: Document for the carriage of containers. Syn: transfer note.

values.label: NATO transit document
values.comment: Customs transit document for the carriage of shipments of the NATO armed forces under Customs supervision.

values.label: Transfrontier waste shipment authorization
values.comment: Document containing the authorization from the relevant authority for the international carriage of waste. Syn: Transfrontier waste shipment permit.

values.label: Transfrontier waste shipment movement document
values.comment: Document certified by the carriers and the consignee to be used for the international carriage of waste.

values.label: End use authorization
values.comment: Document issued by Customs granting the end-use Customs procedure.

values.label: Government contract
values.comment: Document/message describing a contract with a government authority.

values.label: Statistical document, import
values.comment: Document/message describing an import document that is used for statistical purposes.

values.label: Application for documentary credit
values.comment: Message with application for opening of a documentary credit.

values.label: Previous Customs document/message
values.comment: Indication of the previous Customs document/message concerning the same transaction.
